reviews.review: Excellent conclusion to the series that ignores the Rian Johnson travesty.

The first half is a fast and fun romp with excellent chemistry between the main trio (and even C3PO!) However, as the plot begins to slow down we start to see the glaring holes between plot devices.

After 9 fake deaths, 2 macguffins, a programming restriction, and a few more useless plot devices - the audience gets tired of JJ's attempt to tread water and use nostalgia to keep the movie afloat. 

These basic issues, combined with a lack of regard for canon material (Kylo & Poe's comic runs are both neglected + the last jedi is insulted by this movie), leave the end of the Skywalker Saga on a sour note.

I saw the original Star Wars as a kid on opening night at Graumans Chinese Theater. And to have it end like this just pissed me off. Everyone involved with this fiasco needs to be FIRED! They have zero clue of Star Wars and its lore. Forget just the ability to write decent dialogue or even a decent fantasy story. This was written in such a way that there was zero root in reality. Everything is over the top. Rey is basically Jesus now, lmfao. But hey she has had a year to train so it makes total sense. They don't even explain how the emperor survived. The actors did the best they could but with material this bad there is no saving it. The lightsaber duels look like kids in the front yard banging sticks together. The fan service is insulting it is so cheap and blatant. They clearly had no overarching story threads for all 3 when they set out to make this trilogy. It is all over the place. DO NOT GO SEE THIS MOVIE!!!
Pay attention to what people who actually watched the movie are saying, the consensus, on this one...NOT the critics!
The love the small honors to the original trilogy.
Felt like the storyline needed to fill in gaps. It felt like we missed scenes.

I really enjoyed how they wrapped up a lot of questions, except one.  For me it's like the end of an era, my whole life has been finding out how this whole saga plays out, and it couldn't have been better.  There are part that were really intense, I almost couldn't watch.  The characters were great in this one, graphics, and story line as well.  I'm not too critical because I love Star Wars, but this one was GOOD.
Loved it! Reminiscent of the original Star Wars movies. Good humor, excellent fight scenes. Loved that there were cameos of Han, Luke and Leia. Can't wait to see it again.

Felt like JJ was a little modes about episode eight so he made the series his own again at a cost of the first half feeling like you've been thrown into a blender at high-speed but once you're out the smoothie tastes so good and once you've chugged the rest of the edge of your seat smoothie you sit back and reminisce on how this movie left you with the same taste as the first smoothie you got to drink when you were just a little kid and you'd be ok if it was the last real smoothie you ever got.
